

HTTPS SNI Proxy, proxies TLS requests to backend servers based on SNI (server name indication) TLS extension.


Usage: sni_proxy [-c <config>] [-f] [-b <address>] [-p <port>] [-u <user>]
    -c  configruation file, defaults to /etc/sni_proxy.conf
    -f  run in foreground
    -b  listen address, defaults to all addresses
    -p  listen port, defaults to 443
    -u  user to run as, defaults to nobody


Configuration Syntax

<hostname><tab><server address><tab><port><newline>
example.com 192.0.2.10  4343
example.net 2001:DB8::1:10  443


